items.name: SNEnsemble

items.name: Assignment-Anomaly-Detection-in-Industrial-Pipelines-using-Autoencoders
items.description: Industrial pipelines require continuous monitoring to detect faults or anomalies that may lead to equipment failure or safety hazards. In this project, we construct an Autoencoder-based anomaly detection framework using a time-series dataset from the UCI Machine Learning Repository to identify deviations from normal operating conditions.

items.name: Predicting-Road-Surface-Conditions-Using-SAR-Satellite-Imagery-and-Deep-Learning-Models
items.description: This research focuses on predicting road surface conditions using Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) satellite imagery combined with a machine learning framework.  Few-shot learning falls under meta-learning(learning to learn), the way we are able to identify new classes of data easily using only a few examples using our previously learned knowledge.

items.name: Energy-Evaluation---R

items.name: DeepDefender
items.description: DeepDefender is an AI-powered security tool for real-time threat detection using machine learning models. It integrates computer vision for video analysis and provides a simple web interface for monitoring. The project uses frameworks like TensorFlow, PyTorch, and OpenCV to enhance system protection.

items.name: MLOps-Pipeline-Framework
items.description: A generic end-to-end machine learning pipeline framework supporting multiple types of data and learning tasks

items.name: Master-Thesis
items.description: This repository contains a document that reviews popular frameworks for deploying Machine Learning models, focusing on efficiency, compatibility, and performance in production environments.

items.name: Metropolitan-SurrogateModel
items.description: A machine learning framework for efficient metropolitan-scale urban flood prediction combining network clustering with Random Forest surrogate models.

items.name: Chronic-Kidney-Disease-Prediction
items.description: A machine learning framework that predicts the prevalence of a specific chronic disease or health risk factor from digital records of online behavior

items.name: Machine-Learning-Deep-learning-Pipelines
items.description: End-to-end Machine Learning and Deep Learning pipelines from data preprocessing to model evaluation. Includes tools for cleaning data, feature engineering, model training, and performance evaluation. Modular and scalable, supporting frameworks like TensorFlow, PyTorch, and Scikit-learn.

items.name: Chemsy
items.description: A Minimalistic Automatic Framework for Chemometrics and Machine Learning

items.name: ransomware_detection_framework
items.description: A comprehensive framework for ransomware detection and mitigation, integrating AI, machine learning, and multi-layered defense strategies

items.name: consumer-risk-models-python-machine-learning
items.description: Validate consumer risk models with a standardized framework. Create consistent guidelines for machine learning model validation.

items.name: frogbox
items.description: An opinionated machine learning framework.

items.name: Football-Match-Prediction-Home-vs-Away
items.description: This project demonstrates a framework to predict English Premier League match outcomes using machine learning. The project involves data engineering for 30 seasons (1993/1994 to 2022/2023), followed by training and testing models like SVM, Random Forest & Logistic Regression

items.name: Real-Estate-Price-Prediction
items.description: A machine learning project for predicting real estate prices using advanced regression models. This repository includes data preprocessing, feature selection, model training, and evaluation, providing a robust framework for accurate property price estimation. Ideal for data scientists and real estate analysts.

items.name: Google-Advanced-Data-Analytics-Professional-Certificate
items.description: A comprehensive program focused on advanced data analytics techniques, including data visualization, machine learning, and statistical analysis. This course emphasizes practical, hands-on skills using tools such as Python, SQL, and machine learning frameworks to analyze complex datasets and derive actionable insights.

items.name: deep-learning-framework
items.description: Framework to implement machine learning experiments

items.name: ARTSC
items.description: Autoregressive Time Series Classification (ARTSC) ARTSC is a domain-independent machine learning framework for time series classification. By leveraging autoregressive modeling, the method extracts meaningful features to achieve competitive accuracy across diverse datasets. Developed in R, ARTSC provides a simple yet effective solution for research

items.name: FairHealthGrid
items.description: A Python framework for systematic evaluation of bias mitigation strategies in healthcare machine learning applications. The repository contains implementations of a fairness-aware grid search methodology along with comprehensive evaluation tools and examples.

items.name: we_love_streamlit
items.description: This repo include a basic Streamlit use case. Streamlit is an open-source app framework built specifically for Machine Learning and Data Science projects.

items.name: REMEDII-Malware-Detection
items.description: "Robust malware detection system using iterative adversarial training with Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs). This repository implements the REMEDII framework, enhancing the resilience of machine learning-based malware detectors against adversarial attacks, while maintaining high detection accuracy."

items.name: masfi
items.description: Mapping Alternate Scenarios of Forest Intactness (MASFI) is a cloud-based machine learning framework. It uses XGBoost regression and remote sensing data such as GEDI LiDAR to create high-resolution maps and statistics, supporting protected area planning and management.

items.name: atlantic
items.description: Atlantic: Automated Data Preprocessing Framework for Machine Learning

items.name: pennylane-qulacs
items.description: The PennyLane-Qulacs plugin integrates the Qulacs quantum computing framework with PennyLane's quantum machine learning capabilities.

items.name: Parallel_ML_Dask_Spark.
items.description: This repository demonstrates the implementation of traditional machine learning techniques, including XGBoost, Linear Regression, and Random Forest, using distributed frameworks such as Dask and Apache Spark.

items.name: AIML_Research-Intership
items.description: The primary goal of this internship was to leverage SHAP as an XAI framework to interpret machine learning models in diagnosing and predicting heart diseases. The focus is on building trust in AI models by enhancing their transparency and interpretability.

items.name: Research_Internship_code

items.name: TBML
items.description: Tensor Basis Machine Learning (TBML) is a package containing machine learning frameworks for enhancing Reynolds averaged Navier-Stokes predictions of turbulence variables

items.name: DjangoPetClassificationAPI
items.description: Django Rest Framework with Machine Learning Model for Cat and Dog Classification

items.name: pg_plan_inspector
items.description: A framework to monitor and improve the performance of PostgreSQL using Machine Learning methods.

items.name: Office-CCTV-Monitoring
items.description: Initially conceived as an idea for a university project, this initiative transformed into a robust computer vision-powered framework leveraging machine learning, deep learning, and YOLOv8 object detection to classify and track activities like walking, sitting, talking and falling in office environments, enhancing workplace safety and productivity.

items.name: Weather-Research-
items.description: INTEGRATED METEOROLOGICAL SENSING: A SYNERGISTIC FRAMEWORK OF IOT-DRIVEN WEATHER STATIONS AND ADVANCED MACHINE LEARNING ALGORITHMS

items.name: FinanceGPT
items.description: This project focuses on the development of an advanced financial planning chatbot that integrates cutting edge language models and custom machine learning algorithms to deliver personalized financial insights. Utilizing the LangChain framework and the LLaMA language model, the chatbot is designed to engage users in a conversational manner.

items.name: MoleculeBind
items.description: MoleculeBind is a machine-learning framework for chemistry, where we target unifying various molecular representations into one common latent space (SELFIES, SMILES, Graph, Structures, Fingerprints, Molecular Spectra)

items.name: CADIM-
items.description: Cloud-Aware DEM Inundation Mapping (CADIM) : A geospatial framework for flood mapping under cloud cover using machine learning and digital elevation models (DEMs).

items.name: bentoml-ml-architecture
items.description: This repository delves into the inner workings and design principles behind BentoML, a flexible framework for building, packaging, and deploying machine learning models at scale.
